.TH "nvme_update_key" 9 "nvme_update_key" "March 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvme_update_key \- Update key raw data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nvme_update_key
.BI "(struct nvme_global_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "long keyring_id "  ","
.BI "const char *key_type "  ","
.BI "const char *identity "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *key_data "  ","
.BI "int key_len "  ","
.BI "long *key "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
struct nvme_global_ctx object
.IP "keyring_id" 12
Id of the keyring holding key_id
.IP "key_type" 12
Type of the key to insert
.IP "identity" 12
Key identity string
.IP "key_data" 12
Raw data of the key
.IP "key_len" 12
Length of \fIkey_data\fP
.IP "key" 12
Key serial to return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Links the keyring specified by \fIkeyring_id\fP into the session
keyring and updates the key reference by \fIidentity\fP with \fIkey_data\fP.
The old key with identity \fIidentity\fP will be revoked to make it
inaccessible.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or negative error code otherwise
